This overview is intended for new readers, contributors, maintainers, learners, and approved implementation partners.

---

## 2. What Is OPRMT™?

OPRMT™ is a structured prompt engineering framework created by Michael W. Fleming.

It organizes prompt construction and AI instruction design into five controlled components:

```text
O — Objective
P — Parameters
R — Results
M — Method
T — Tools
```

The framework is designed to make prompts clearer, more repeatable, more auditable, and easier to evaluate.

---

## 3. Why OPRMT™ Exists

Unstructured prompts often fail because they lack:

- Clear task definition
- Defined input boundaries
- Output requirements
- Execution process
- Tool limits
- Review criteria
- Version control
- Reusable structure

OPRMT™ exists to reduce prompt ambiguity and convert AI instructions into structured technical assets.

---

## 4. Framework Components

| Component | Purpose | Primary Question |
|---|---|---|
| Objective | Defines the task or outcome | What must be accomplished? |
| Parameters | Defines inputs, constraints, and boundaries | What must the system know or obey? |
| Results | Defines expected output or deliverable | What should the output look like? |
| Method | Defines process or execution steps | How should the work be completed? |
| Tools | Defines allowed resources and systems | What tools or sources may be used? |

